Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, SheetJS (xlsx).

Structure:
app/layout.tsx
app/page.tsx
app/globals.css
lib/compare.ts
components/FileUpload.tsx
components/ResultsTable.tsx
components/StatsBar.tsx
components/DownloadButton.tsx

Rules:
- 'use client' on all components
- No server components, no API routes
- No extra packages beyond: next react typescript tailwindcss xlsx
- No inline styles except SheetJS cell fill hex values
- No any types — use types from lib/compare.ts via @/lib/compare
- No useEffect for data — use useMemo
- No rendering >50 rows — paginate always
- lib/compare.ts must be pure TS, no React, no imports
- Parse xlsx: { type:'array', raw:false } — all values as strings
- Compare cells: trim().toString() both sides
- Always sort both files by sku before comparing
- Ambra = source of truth

Colors:
- Brand: #3b5bdb
- Changed: bg-amber-100 text-amber-900
- Missing: bg-red-100 text-red-900
- Added: bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-900

Types (lib/compare.ts):
- CellStatus = 'match'|'changed'|'added'|'missing'
- DiffCell = { aify:string; ambra:string; status:CellStatus }
- DiffRow = { sku:string; rowStatus:CellStatus; cells:Record<string,DiffCell> }
- CompareResult = { columns:string[]; rows:DiffRow[]; stats:{ total:number; matched:number; changed:number; added:number; missing:number } }
